# Backend isolation (ToonExpo)

**Source of truth:** `docs/TECH_CARD.md`, `docs/01-ARCHITECTURE.md`, `AGENTS.md`.

If older docs (`docs/PROGRESS.md` history, `docs/reference/*`, sprint notes) mention Auth.js, Prisma in `apps/web`, or Next.js `app/api` routes for business logic — **ignore them**. Prefer Nest.

## Hard boundaries

- **`apps/api` (NestJS)** — only runtime that may use Prisma (`@toonexpo/db`), `DATABASE_URL`, `AUTH_SECRET`, R2, Resend, Upstash Redis, BOS secrets.
- **`apps/web` (Next.js)** — UI + typed HTTP client only. Allowed env: `APP_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` (default `/nest`), `API_URL` (rewrite target), Sentry public/DSN as documented. **No** Prisma, argon2, next-auth/Auth.js, AWS SDK, private Redis/R2/BOS keys.
- Browser → same-origin **`/nest/*`** rewrite → Nest. Session cookie: Nest httpOnly DB sessions (`toonexpo.sid`) + CSRF double-submit.
- Thin `'use server'` wrappers may call Nest via `serverApiRequest` — they must **not** touch the database.

## Never do (regressions)

- Add `apps/web/src/app/api/**` for product APIs.
- Import `@toonexpo/db` / Prisma from `apps/web`.
- Reintroduce Auth.js / NextAuth in web.
- Put infrastructure secrets in web env or client bundles.
- “Wire Nest to Auth.js sessions” — auth **is** Nest DB sessions already.

## Where new backend work goes

| Concern | Place |
|---|---|
| Auth, CRM, catalog, QR, uploads, admin, analytics, exhibition, visual-map, favorites, partner, builder, buyer | Nest module under `apps/api/src/modules/*` |
| Shared DTOs / Zod | `packages/contracts` |
| Schema / migrations | `packages/db` |
| UI calling API | `apps/web/src/lib/api/*` + feature `lib/*` wrappers |

## Before large changes

Read `docs/TECH_CARD.md` auth/backend rows and architecture hard rules. Do not follow sprint history that contradicts them.
